cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the classification and reporting of chest X-rays using both image and text data. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The proposed TieNet model also involves attention mechanisms and end-to-end training, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper utilizes free-text radiological reports, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
